<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-5324] AdminClient: add close with timeout, fix some timeout bugs</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-5324</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Add a close method with a timeout, similar to some other APIs.  Close waits for all calls to complete.  Once the timeout expires, all calls are aborted.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Fix a minor bug which made it impossible to have per-call timeouts which were longer than the default timeout.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Fix a minor bug where we could oversleep short timeouts because we didn&apos;t adjust the polling interval based on the extant timeouts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Add some unit tests for timeouts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
